Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 13/8/2024

1. Introduction

Welcome to the Mchezo App. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our application. By using the Mchezo App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

2. •  Registration Information:
•	Email Address: Collected when you register for an account.
•	Password: Collected to authenticate your account.
•	User ID: Generated by Firebase Authentication upon successful registration.
•  Profile Information:
•	Name: Collected during profile completion (first name, last name).
•	Phone Number: Collected during profile completion.
•	NIDA ID: Collected during profile completion for identification purposes.
•	Gender: Collected during profile completion.
•	Group: Collected during profile completion to associate you with a group.
•	Role: Admin or User role is assigned based on the profile completion (for admin functionality).
•  Transaction and Activity Data:
•	Deposit and Withdrawal Information: Collected related to your transactions within the app.
•	Group Activities: Data related to your interactions within your group.
3. How We Use Your Information

•  To Provide and Maintain the Service:
•	Account Management: We use your email and password to create and manage your account.
•	Profile Management: Your profile information (name, phone number, NIDA ID, gender, and group) is used to complete and maintain your profile.
•  To Communicate with You:
•	Notifications: We may send you notifications regarding updates, changes, and offers related to the app.
•  For Security:
•	Fraud Prevention: Your data is used to monitor for fraudulent activities and ensure the safety of our users.
•  To Analyze Usage:
•	App Improvement: Usage data and activity within the app are analyzed to enhance user experience and app functionality.

4. How We Share Your Information
1.	With Administrators:
o	Profile Access: Admins may access certain information to manage groups and transactions.
2.	Service Providers:
o	Third-Party Services: We share information with third-party services, such as Firebase, which help us operate the app.
3.	Legal Requirements:
o	Compliance: We may disclose your information if required by law or to protect our rights.

5. Data Security
Firebase Authentication: Your email and password are securely stored and managed by Firebase Authentication, which uses industry-standard security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access.

We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.

6. Your Rights
Access and Update: You can access and update your personal information through the app.
Delete Account: You may request to delete your account and personal information at any time.
7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.

8. Contact Us

For any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at gkyando5@gmail.com.

